                <supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucius</ex></expan> Vo</supplied>lusius <expan><abbr>Q</abbr><ex>uinti</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan> Sa<supplied reason="lost">turninus VIIvir <expan><abbr>epulon</abbr><ex>um</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>co</abbr><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ul</ex></expan> IIIvir</supplied> <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr><supplied reason="lost">c</supplied>enturi</abbr><ex>i</ex>s</expan> equ<supplied reason="lost">itum recognoscendis <expan><abbr>cens</abbr><ex>oria</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pot</abbr><ex>estate</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="3"/><supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucius</ex></expan> V</supplied>olusius <expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>uci</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan> Sa<supplied reason="lost">turninus <expan><abbr>co</abbr><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ul</ex></expan> augur <expan><abbr>proco</abbr><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ul</ex></expan> Asiae</supplied> <lb n="4"/><supplied reason="lost">te</supplied>mplum divo Augusto <supplied reason="lost">faciendum curaverunt <expan><abbr>idemq</abbr><ex>ue</ex></expan> dedicaverunt</supplied>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>2 aneinanderpassende Fragmente; Maße beziehen sich auf Fragment a; Maße Fragment b: 44,5 x 39 x 5 cm. Datierung: L. Volusius Q.f. Saturninus: cos. 12 v. Chr., gestorben 20 n. Chr.; gleichnamiger Sohn: cos. 3 n. Chr. Zu Status und Ämtern von L. Volusius Saturninus Vater und Sohn: Tac., ann. 3, 30, 1; Suet., Aug. 37; AE 1914, 0136 = ILS 9483. Ergänzungen nach Di Stefano Manzella, der noch einen alternativen Ergänzungsvorschlag macht: [L(ucius) Vo]lusius Q(uinti) f(ilius) Sa[turninus triumvir] / [c]enturis equ[itum legendis] / [L(ucius) V]olusius L(uci) f(ilius) Sa[turninus consul] / [te]mplum divo Augusto [faciendum curaverunt]. Material: lunensischer Marmor.</p>
            </div>
